 The team dressed in tutus and tekkies in support of the BNI CANSA Tutus and Tekkies fun runs, which took place over the weekend. They also sold hot dogs and cold drinks in front of the store during the day to raise additional funds for CANSA, and customers eagerly supported the team initiative for a good cause. ALSO READ:CANSA promotes a healthy lifestyle Cruchenka Mulligan, sales administrator at Stewarts and Lloyds Nelspruit, explained that they decided to support it and to involve their customers to give back to the community. ALSO READ:Hope picnic in aid for cancer They sold boerie rolls at R20 apiece, for which customers received a free sticker of their choice, and cold drinks at R10, donating all the proceeds to CANSA.